Problem Statement

Develop a Java application to simulate an ATM withdrawal system using exception handling. The program should store the account holder's name, account number, and available balance. If the withdrawal amount exceeds the available balance, display an appropriate message by throwing and handling an exception. 
Otherwise, complete the transaction and display the remaining balance.

package Raghul;

import java.util.*;

class ATM {

    String accountHolder = "Raghul";
    int accountNumber = 10059;
    double balance = 5000;

    void withdraw(double amount) {

        try {

            if (amount > balance) {
                throw new Exception("Insufficient Balance");
            }

            balance = balance - amount;

            System.out.println("Withdrawal Successful");
            System.out.println("Remaining Balance : " + balance);

        }

        catch (Exception e) {

            System.out.println(e.getMessage());

        }

    }

    void display() {

        System.out.println("Account Holder : " + accountHolder);
        System.out.println("Account Number : " + accountNumber);
        System.out.println("Available Balance : " + balance);

    }

}

public class ATMTransaction {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        ATM atm = new ATM();

        atm.display();

        System.out.println();

        System.out.println("Withdraw Amount : 7000");

        atm.withdraw(7000);

    }

}
